modules.description: This module enables sending and receiving file descriptors over UNIX domain sockets using `send_fd`, `recv_fd`, and their variants. It operates on `Unix.file_descr`, `bytes`, `string`, and `Unix.msg_flag` types, facilitating low-level inter-process communication. Concrete use cases include passing open file descriptors between processes, such as sharing network sockets or file handles with a child process.
